From a6c93961750610d87bd0ac1604493f384c1c4c88 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: patamin <patamin@gmail.com>
Date: Wed, 24 Jun 2026 17:03:21 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Fix PDF export 500 (middleware /fonts/* gap), GMT+7
 timestamps, and match print layout to PDF

- middleware matcher now excludes /fonts/* so server-side font fetches
  during PDF render are not redirected to /login (root cause of the
  live PDF export 500)
- add formatThaiDateTime() (explicit Asia/Bangkok timeZone) and use it
  everywhere a timestamp is shown, replacing bare toLocaleString('th-TH')
  calls that rendered 7 hours behind on Vercel's UTC clock
- add print-view.tsx: print-only layout mirroring the approved PDF
  report structure, shown via window.print(); hide the app sidebar and
  on-screen card UI when printing
- wrap export route handlers in try/catch so failures return a
  diagnosable JSON error instead of a bare 500
